{"hits": {"hits": [{"created": "2026-01-09T01:46:59.079041+00:00", "modified": "2026-01-09T01:46:59.640836+00:00", "id": 18193075, "conceptrecid": "18193074", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.18193075", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.18193074", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18193075", "metadata": {"title": "Tourism, biodiversity and protected areas - Review from northern Fennoscandia", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.18193075", "publication_date": "2016", "description": "(Uploaded by Plazi for the IPBES Invasive Alien Species Assessment) Tourist numbers in northern Fennoscandia outweigh those in other northern boreal - arctic regions, which creates a specific need to evaluate the impacts of tourism. This review 1) identifies patterns and trends in the vegetation and wildlife of northern Fennoscandian terrestrial ecosystems as a consequence of tourism and recreation, 2) discusses the implications of findings in terms of the intensity, area and magnitude of impacts, changing climate and management needs under increasing tourist pressure, and 3) identifies research gaps. The reviewed studies show negative environmental and biodiversity impacts that are most pronounced near tourist resorts. The most sensitive plants, birds and mammals decline or disappear from the disturbed sites, and the species composition shifts from `wild' species to cultural and human associated species. There is little research on the spread of alien species, but the few examples show that alien species can be promoted by tourism activities. Impacts of the use of motorized vehicles have not been widely studied either, despite the extensive track network which can cause disturbance to wildlife. The integrated impacts of tourism and climate change on the vegetation and wildlife was not addressed directly in any of the reviewed studies. In addition, little research has been done on carrying out restoration at tourist areas. Scientific research on these topics is needed to prevent, minimize or restore the most negative ecological impacts of tourism and recreation. (C) 2015 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Tolvanen, Anne", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kangas, Katja", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Chapter 2", "biodiversity", "environment assessment", "IPBES", "Alien Invasive Species Assessment AIS", "invasive species"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/4b859a7856b166aea72e2481da9d27e0", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/ddfc8812638ca7656c0c4c733835f50aa8e414bb2d3b20f4e4bbb49d7f6f2fed", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/2352922/items/TU4P33JM", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/2352922/items/TU4P33JM", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/b79e4fcfebf578895353c7ba22874284!/b14802-18799", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/359bd494433933b868f85e88d3437f76", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.1016/j.jenvman.2015.12.011", "relation": "isVariantFormOf", "resource_type": "publication", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.7430682", "relation": "isCitedBy", "resource_type": "publication-report", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"pages": "58-66", "title": "Journal of Environmental Management", "volume": "169"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/4b859a7856b166aea72e2481da9d27e0"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:2352922:items:TU4P33JM"}, {"identifier": "10.1016/j.jenvman.2015.12.011"}], "communities": [{"id": "ipbes-ias"}, {"id": "biosyslit"}], "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_las